Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph

SpineDigest CLI

Purpose:
  Create and operate portable Wiki Graph archives for AI agents.
  Treat `.wikg` as the managed archive. Use commands to mutate or inspect it; do not edit archive internals directly.

Object model:
  Search and navigation return URI-addressable objects. Common object kinds are:
    meta, chapter, chapter-tree, entity, triple, source, summary, chunk

Object workflow:
  - `search` returns candidate Wiki Graph URIs from query text.
  - `list` is search without query text: it enumerates objects from a located Wiki Graph URI or lens URI.
  - `get` opens one readable URI.
  - `related` expands from one URI to nearby URIs.
  - `evidence` traces a URI to source-backed evidence.
  - `pack` builds bounded Agent-readable context around one graph object URI.

Object commands:
  wikigraph <located-wkg-uri> search <query> [--limit <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--evidence [n]] [--backlinks] [--json|--jsonl]
  wikigraph <located-wkg-uri>/<chapter|entity|triple|source|summary|chunk> search <query> [--limit <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--evidence [n]] [--backlinks] [--json|--jsonl]
  wikigraph <located-wkg-uri>/triple/<subject|_>/<predicate|_>/<object|_> search <query> [--limit <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--evidence [n]] [--json|--jsonl]
  wikigraph <located-wkg-uri>/<chapter|entity|triple|source|summary|chunk> list [--limit <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--evidence [n]] [--backlinks] [--json|--jsonl]
  wikigraph <located-wkg-uri>/triple/<subject|_>/<predicate|_>/<object|_> list [--limit <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--evidence [n]] [--json|--jsonl]
  wikigraph <object-uri> get [--evidence [n]] [--backlinks] [--json|--jsonl]
  wikigraph <chunk-uri|entity-uri> related [query] [--role <any|subject|object|self>] [--evidence [n]] [--json|--jsonl]
  wikigraph <entity|triple|summary|chunk-uri> evidence [query] [--limit <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--json|--jsonl]
  wikigraph next <cursor> [--limit <n>] [--json|--jsonl]
  wikigraph next <wikigraph-uri-with-wikg-locator> <cursor> [--limit <n>] [--json|--jsonl]
  wikigraph <located-chunk-uri|located-entity-uri> pack [--budget <chars>] [--json|--jsonl]

URI requirement:
  `search`, `list`, `get`, `related`, `evidence`, and `pack` use Wiki Graph URIs, not bare filesystem paths.
  Read `wikigraph help uri` before using these commands; skipping the URI rules commonly leads to invalid commands.

Archive commands:
  wikigraph <archive-uri> create [source] [--input-format <format>] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>]
  wikigraph <archive-uri> export --output-format <format> [--output <path>]
  wikigraph <archive-uri> estimate [--stage <source|reading-graph|reading-summary>] [--json]
  wikigraph <archive-uri>/state get [--json]
  wikigraph transform [--input <path>] [--output <path>] [--input-format <format>] [--output-format <format>] [--digest-dir <path>] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>] [--stage <stage>] [--verbose|-v]

Generation queue:
  wikigraph <chapter-uri> queue add --task <reading-graph|reading-summary|knowledge-graph> --accept-cost [--boost] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>]
  wikigraph wkg-job:// list [--all] [--active]
  wikigraph wkg-job://<job-id> get [--json]
  wikigraph wkg-job://<job-id> watch [--jsonl] [--from beginning|now]
  Queue generation tasks call an LLM, consume tokens, and may incur provider charges.

Maintenance:
  wikigraph <archive-uri> get [--json|--jsonl]
  wikigraph <archive-uri> set [metadata options] [--llm <json>]
  wikigraph <cover-uri> get
  wikigraph <chapter-collection-uri> add|list [options]
  wikigraph <chapter-uri>/state get [--json]
  wikigraph <chapter-uri> move|remove|reset [options]
  wikigraph <chapter-uri>/source set [--input <path>] --input-format <format>
  wikigraph <chapter-uri>/summary set [--input <path>]
  wikigraph <chapter-uri>/title set (--title <title>|--clear)
  wikigraph <archive-uri>/chapter/tree get|set [options]
  wikigraph config status [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
    Prints JSON by default and does not accept `--json`.
  wikigraph help [topic] [--help|-h]

Help contract:
  - Append `--help` to commands and subcommands to see command-specific usage.
  - Use `wikigraph help <topic>` for cross-command concepts, constraints, and runtime behavior.
  - Treat `wikigraph --help` as the root page of the same help system.

